activity to regulate our

42
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:31,029
body temperature usually at a temperature
higher than the surrounding environment.

43
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:37,480
Every metabolic reaction that takes place
in our body is only about 25% efficient.

44
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:44,100
That means that 75% of the energy used to
do the reaction is given off as heat.

45
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:48,090
We trap a portion of that heat as needed
in our body to keep ourselves warm.

46
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:54,040
We're also constantly losing heat to the
environment through radiation, conduction,

47
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:56,440
convection and evaporation.

48
00:02:56,440 --> 00:03:00,290
Radiation is the loss of heat through
infrared rays.

49
00:03:00,290 --> 00:03:04,250
Conduction is the transfer of heat between
solid materials like sitting on

50
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,860
a cold bench.

51
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:10,400
Convection removes heat with the flow of
air or water across our skin.

52
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:14,500
And evaporation is the loss of heat
through a phase change from liquid to gas,

53
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,190
like with sweat.

54
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:19,090
The four methods of heat transfer take on
a different level of

55
00:03:19,090 --> 00:03:22,570
importance based on multiple factors such
