64
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:55,390
Whether you're in the water or air also
makes a difference.

65
00:03:55,390 --> 00:03:59,610
Water conducts heat away from the body 25
or more times faster than air,

66
00:03:59,610 --> 00:04:03,050
thus shortening both time to hypothermia
and survival time.

67
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:07,040
Movement of the air or wind across your
skin means more air

68
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:10,400
molecules touching you, so faster removal
of heat.

69
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:14,480
The air that is warmed by your skin then
moves on being replaced with

70
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:17,040
colder air which again draws heat from
your body.

71
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:21,630
There are charts available online that
show how much colder it feels for

72
